    <main id="main-content"  class="ds-region-middle order-1 mobile--order-0">
        <div id="block-fdic-theme-content" class="block block-system block-system-main-block">
  
    
      <article class="node--wholepage">
  
    

  
  <div>
    
		<div class="field field--name-field-content field--type-entity-reference-revisions field--label-hidden field__items">
			<div class="field__item">  <div class="paragraph paragraph--type--text paragraph--view-mode--default">
          <p>
                            The FDIC offers many economic and financial resources through its public web site. This Bank Data Guide is a summary of the tools that are
                            available.
                        </p>
<p><a href="/resources/tools/bank-data-guide/guide.pdf">Bank Data Guide</a>
</p>
<p>
                            Many of these products also offer the following:
                            </p><ul>
<li class="list-style-none">
                                    a free <a href="https://service.govdelivery.com/accounts/USFDIC/subscriber/new">subscription</a> service to be notified of news or updates
                                </li>
<li class="list-style-none">
                                    product specific help pages
                                </li>
<li class="list-style-none">
                                    on-line assistance through the <a href="https://ask.fdic.gov/fdicinformationandsupportcenter/s/fdicdirform?language=en_US">Question, Suggestion, Requests</a> links
                                </li>
</ul>
<p>
                            The FDIC has modified a few of our data products - BankFind Suite, Institution Financial Reports, Peer Group Comparisons, Summary of Deposits,
                            Historic Bank Data, and Events and Changes. Features now include enhanced navigation, an API to enable streamlined access to data and
                            consolidated Help pages.
                        </p>
<p>
                            A complete list of our products are available at: <a href="/bank/">https://www.fdic.gov/bank/</a>
</p>
<p>
                            Other products available include
                            
                            the <a href="/resources/tools/bank-data-guide/quick-reference-table.html">Quick Reference Table</a>.
                        </p>
<p>PDF files on this page reference Portable Document Format (PDF) files.
Adobe Acrobat, a reader available for free on the Internet, is required to display or print PDF files. <a href="/acrobat.html"> (PDF Help)</a></p>

      </div>
</div></div>

  </div>
</article>

